<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Schools" statutenumber="79-555"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>79-555</statuteno><catchline>Class III school district; board of education; meetings; when held.</catchline><para>The regular meetings of the board of education of a Class III school district shall be held as provided in section 79-554. Special meetings may be held as circumstances may demand, and all meetings of the board shall be open to the public.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1881, c. 78, subdivision XIV, &#167; 6, p. 379; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 6953; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 6587; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 79-2506; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 79-2508; </para><para>Laws 1947, c. 291, &#167; 1, p. 903; </para><para>Laws 1949, c. 256, &#167; 238, p. 770; </para><para>Laws 1961, c. 402, &#167; 2, p. 1218; </para><para>Laws 1965, c. 525, &#167; 1, p. 1656; </para><para>Laws 1972, LB 1268, &#167; 2; </para><para>Laws 1982, LB 892, &#167; 1; </para><para>R.S.1943, (1994), &#167; 79-805; </para><para>Laws 1996, LB 900, &#167; 308. </para></source></law></legaldoc>